"title": "5681: family, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5681",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A unit ordained by God for the comfort and protection of its members. It is usually a group of relatives, but the people of God are also seen as a family.</p>\n<h2>The scope of the family in Scripture</h2>\n<h3>The family unit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:7\">GEN 43:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:1\">EXO 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:3\">EXO 12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:2\">JDG 11:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:21\">1SA 1:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam27:3\">1SA 27:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:3\">2SA 2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:15\">1KI 17:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr13:14\">1CH 13:14</a> <em>The family of Obed-Edom is blessed by the presence of the ark</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:27\">PRO 27:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:15\">PRO 31:15</a> <em>The wife of noble character provides for her family</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:21\">MRK 3:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:52\">LUK 12:52</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:33-Acts16:34\">ACT 16:33–16:34</a> <em>The Philippian jailer and his family are baptised</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:8\">1TI 5:8</a></p>\n<h3>The extended family or clan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:37-Gen24:38\">GEN 24:37–24:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:40\">GEN 24:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:27\">GEN 46:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:22\">GEN 50:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:2\">NUM 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:1\">NUM 18:1</a> <em>the priesthood of Aaron and his family</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:5\">DEU 25:5</a> <em>Levirate marriage provides for the continuity of the family</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:17-Josh2:18\">JOS 2:17–2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:23\">JOS 6:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:25\">JOS 6:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam22:22\">1SA 22:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:14\">1KI 14:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:1\">2KI 11:1</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr22:10\">2CH 22:10</a> <em>Athaliah destroys the royal family of Judah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:16\">EZR 10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer35:3\">JER 35:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:17\">JER 38:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:3\">DAN 1:3</a></p>\n<h3>The descendants of any individual</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:42\">JHN 7:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:10\">DEU 25:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:29\">JOS 13:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:31-1Sam2:32\">1SA 2:31–2:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:36\">1SA 2:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam3:11-1Sam3:13\">1SA 3:11–3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:7\">DAN 11:7</a></p>\n<h3>The people of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:10-Heb2:15\">HEB 2:10–2:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:22\">PSA 22:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:1\">AMO 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:10\">GAL 6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:17\">1PE 4:17</a></p>\n<h2>Marriage obligations and restrictions within the family</h2>\n<h3>Marriage within the wider family circle was preferable in early times</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg14:3\">JDG 14:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:1-Gen24:9\">GEN 24:1–24:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:37\">GEN 24:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:40\">GEN 24:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:46-Gen28:2\">GEN 27:46–28:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:6-Gen28:9\">GEN 28:6–28:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:1\">EXO 2:1</a></p>\n<h3>Incestuous marriage was forbidden</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:6-Lev18:18\">LEV 18:6–18:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:17\">LEV 20:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:19-Lev20:21\">LEV 20:19–20:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:20-Deut27:23\">DEU 27:20–27:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:3\">MAT 14:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:17\">MRK 6:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:1-1Cor5:5\">1CO 5:1–5:5</a></p>\n<h3>The obligation to marry the widow of a dead brother</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:5-Deut25:10\">DEU 25:5–25:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:8-Gen38:10\">GEN 38:8–38:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:19-Ruth2:20\">RUT 2:19–2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:1-Ruth4:10\">RUT 4:1–4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:23-Matt22:32\">MAT 22:23–22:32</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:18-Mark12:27\">MRK 12:18–12:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:27-Luke20:38\">LUK 20:27–20:38</a></p>\n<h2>Laws of inheritance kept property within the family</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:1-Num27:11\">NUM 27:1–27:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:25-Lev25:28\">LEV 25:25–25:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:13-Job42:15\">JOB 42:13–42:15</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of family solidarity</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:8-Gen14:16\">GEN 14:8–14:16</a> <em>Abraham and Lot</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:31-2Sam18:33\">2SA 18:31–18:33</a> <em>David and Absalom</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:11-Ruth1:18\">RUT 1:11–1:18</a> <em>Naomi and Ruth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:13\">NEH 4:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:12-Acts23:24\">ACT 23:12–23:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:3-1Tim5:4\">1TI 5:3–5:4</a> <em>Family solidarity is encouraged.</em></p>",
